job_posting.full_description:
Are you a visionary leader with a passion for advancing public health and improving population health outcomes? If you’re an experienced Public Health and Preventive Medicine professional with strong communication and collaboration skills, the Saskatchewan Ministry of Health invites you to join our team as
Deputy Chief Medical Health Officer.
About Us
The Saskatchewan Ministry of Health is committed to improving the health and well-being of all Saskatchewan residents. Guided by the principles of
Better Health, Better Care, Better Value, and Better Teams
, the Ministry sets provincial strategies, establishes policy and legislative frameworks, and ensures the delivery of high-quality, patient-centred health services.
The Opportunity
As one of two Deputy Chief Medical Health Officers, reporting to the Chief Medical Health Officer (CMHO), you will play a key leadership role in advancing public health priorities, protecting population health, and driving health equity across Saskatchewan.
In this critical role, you will:
Provide expert medical and public health leadership
to develop and implement policies, standards, and programs including health assessment and measurement, health promotion, disease and injury prevention and health protection;
Monitor and report on population health
and respond to emerging health challenges, ensuring alignment with evidence-based practices;
Collaborate
with key partners, including the Saskatchewan Health Authority (SHA), other ministries, Indigenous governments and organizations, and national and international stakeholders;
Support legislative responsibilities
and the Chief MHO to administer the legislated functions and responsibilities of the position as outlined in
The Public Health Act, 1994
and regulations;
Act as a spokesperson
on public health matters, representing Saskatchewan in federal/provincial/territorial committees and providing trusted advice to decision-makers; and
Contribute to research and education
, supporting capacity building in the field of public health and supervising students and residents, with potential academic appointment opportunities at the University of Saskatchewan’s College of Medicine.
Qualifications and Requirements
To succeed in this role, you will bring:
A medical degree recognized in Canada;
Fellowship with the Royal College of Physicians and Surgeons of Canada in Public Health and Preventive Medicine;
Eligibility for licensure to practice as a specialist in Public Health and Preventive Medicine in Saskatchewan with the College of Physicians and Surgeons of Saskatchewan;
Demonstrated experience providing strategic leadership in public health, including developing and implementing health programs, policies, or strategies;
Expertise in epidemiology, health surveillance, and population health assessment;
Experience in stakeholder engagement and collaboration across diverse sectors, including government, health authorities, Indigenous communities, and non-governmental organizations;
Comprehensive knowledge of public health and preventive medicine principles, including health promotion, disease prevention, and communicable disease control;
Strong ethical standards, integrity, and credibility within the public health community;
Exceptional communication, interpersonal, and collaborative skills to build networks and engage effectively with stakeholders;
Analytical and strategic thinking abilities to address complex public health challenges; and
Familiarity with Saskatchewan’s health system or experience in government/public health settings is an asset.
What We Offer
By joining the Saskatchewan Ministry of Health, you will have the opportunity to:
Lead transformative public health initiatives and shape policies that directly impact the health and well-being of Saskatchewan residents;
Work in a dynamic and multidisciplinary environment with diverse stakeholders across sectors; and
Contribute to building healthier communities and driving positive change.
We offer an attractive compensation package, including:
Competitive salary;
Comprehensive benefits package; and
Pension plan.
Diversity and Inclusion
The Saskatchewan Ministry of Health values diversity and is committed to fostering an inclusive, respectful, and harassment-free workplace. The Ministry values diversity and encourages applicants from underrepresented groups, including Indigenous peoples, persons with disabilities, and visible minorities.
